<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-may-14-2025/"><img class="wp-image-254033 size-thumbnail aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Screenshot-2025-05-13-at-3.29.28 PM-150x150.png" alt="hero’s journey" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://aeon.co/essays/why-does-every-film-and-tv-series-seem-to-have-the-same-plot?utm_source=rss-feed" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The many faces of the hero’s journey</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/05/13/opinion/trump-firing-hayden.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">George Saunders responds to Trump’s firing of Librarian of Congress, Carla Hayden</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://lareviewofbooks.org/article/sneering-at-or-with-the-white-lotus/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Sneering in </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">The White Lotu</span></i></a></li>
